<div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-25_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-26_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-28_">Here at The Mandatory Training Group, we receive many enquiries from people across the UK asking about mandatory and statutory training. Many find these two terms quite confusing and often ask:</span></p><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-29_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-31_">“Is there really a difference between statutory and mandatory training?”What are the examples of statutory training?</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-34_">What is the difference between statutory and mandatory training?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/pexelsekaterinabolovtsova6077326-1671779620993.jpg?v=1671779630" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/pexelsekaterinabolovtsova6077326-1671779620993.jpg?v=1671779630 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/pexelsekaterinabolovtsova6077326-1671779620993_500x.jpg?v=1671779630 320w" width="5472" height="3648" alt="Is there a difference between mandatory and statutory training? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Is there a difference between mandatory and statutory training? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-35_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-38_">Admittedly, the words ‘mandatory’ and ‘statutory’ have similarities but also significant differences, especially regarding compliance training, such as health and safety at work training.
<br><br>
We looked at various dictionaries to see how they define "statutory" and "mandatory". We also reviewed several compliance-related websites and found that ‘mandatory’ and ‘statutory’ are used interchangeably as if they mean the same thing. What was clear was that statutory training is mandatory, while mandatory training is not necessarily statutory.
<br><br>
Before we further explain these similarities and differences, let’s start by looking at the dictionary definitions of ‘statutory’ and ‘mandatory’.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-41_">How are ‘statutory’ and ‘mandatory’ defined in the dictionaries?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingelearningcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642414264900-1671519057872.jpg?v=1671519171" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingelearningcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642414264900-1671519057872.jpg?v=1671519171 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingelearningcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642414264900-1671519057872_500x.jpg?v=1671519171 320w" width="7952" height="5304" alt="How do you differentiate mandatory training and statutory training? - Dr Richard Dune - " title="How do you differentiate mandatory training and statutory training? - Dr Richard Dune - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-42_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-45_">The Collins Dictionary defines the words ‘statutory’ and ‘mandatory’ as follows:</span></p><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-46_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-48_">"Statutory relates to rules or laws which have been formally written down"<br><br>

"Mandatory relates to actions or procedures that people have to do because it is a rule or a law"</span></p><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-51_">The Oxford Dictionary defines ‘statutory’ and ‘mandatory’ as follows:</span></p><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-52_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-54_">"Statutory - required, permitted, or enacted by statute"
<br><br>
"Mandatory - required by law or mandate; compulsory"</span></p><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-55_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-57_">After reviewing these definitions, we felt that they did not clearly distinguish between "statutory" and "mandatory". Hence, the confusion regarding statutory and mandatory training.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h2 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-60_">What is statutory and mandatory training?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642417021129-1671519057451.jpg?v=1671519098" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642417021129-1671519057451.jpg?v=1671519098 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingthemandatorytraininggroupuk1642417021129-1671519057451_500x.jpg?v=1671519098 320w" width="5435" height="3623" alt="Mandatory and statutory training courses provider in the UK - Dr Richard Dune - " title="Mandatory and statutory training courses provider in the UK - Dr Richard Dune - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-61_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-62_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-64_">This section will provide more concise definitions of ‘statutory training’ and ‘mandatory training’. We will also give statutory and mandatory training examples, which will help us distinguish between these types.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h2 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-67_">What is statutory training?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingelearningcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk21642418348961-1671519057776.jpg?v=1671519152" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingelearningcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk21642418348961-1671519057776.jpg?v=1671519152 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/whatisthedifferencebetweenstatutoryandmandatorytrainingelearningcoursesthemandatorytraininggroupuk21642418348961-1671519057776_500x.jpg?v=1671519152 320w" width="5555" height="3703" alt="Mandatory and statutory training courses - CPD Certified - Dr Richard Dune - " title="Mandatory and statutory training courses - CPD Certified - Dr Richard Dune - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-68_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-71_">Statutory training is where a statutory body has mandated that organisations provide that training based on specific legislation. The most common sources of statutory training are the Health and Safety at Work Act etc. 1974, and the Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999.
